text.paragraph:
In general, opioids should not be abruptly discontinued. [See 


                                 DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION (2.5)

                              ]

Morphine sulfate may cause miosis, even in total darkness. Pinpoint pupils are a sign of opioid overdose but are not pathognomonic (e.g., pontine lesions of hemorrhagic or ischemic origin may produce similar findings). Marked mydriasis rather than miosis may be seen with hypoxia in overdose situations. [See 

                              CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY (12)
                           ]
